Urho compatible solution you can change the shadow intensity for darker or brighter shadows. The above image uses 0.5f for shadowIntensity\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":11,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-01-02T17:20:54.934Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":10,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":29,"readers_count":28,"score":10.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":4007,"topic_slug":"alternatives-to-dynamic-shadows","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":247,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":34819,"name":"","username":"GodMan","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/g/e79b87/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-01-02T17:56:38.500Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eLet us know when you upload. I would like to test it for you.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":12,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-01-02T17:56:38.500Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":11,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":30,"readers_count":29,"score":6.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":4007,"topic_slug":"alternatives-to-dynamic-shadows","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Dave82","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/dave82/{size}/2369_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":861,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":34820,"name":"Golden Thumbs","username":"GoldenThumbs","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/goldenthumbs/{size}/1669_2.png","created_at":"2020-01-02T19:30:09.675Z","cooked":"\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ein 90% of the situations standard lights (spot , point and directional) can‚Äôt reproduce the dark ambience of a horror game level.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI disagree. Look at Doom 3. I feel it pulls off a horror atmosphere wonderfully and it only uses dynamic lights.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":13,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-01-02T19:30:09.675Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":30,"readers_count":29,"score":11.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":4007,"topic_slug":"alternatives-to-dynamic-shadows","display_username":"Golden Thumbs","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1004,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":34821,"name":"Jonathan","username":"Sinoid","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/f19dbf/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-01-02T22:15:18.422Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003eDark ambience != dark\u003c/code\u003e. The cabin above the shark-tank in the RE remake comes to mind as dark-ambience, it‚Äôs lit but more gloomy glow than DOOM3‚Äôs hard edges everywhere.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/dave82\"\u003e@Dave82\u003c/a\u003e how fat is a single view (color + depth, etc)? Really love prerendered backgrounds, would love to see retro in the style become a thing.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":14,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-01-02T22:15:18.422Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":13,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":26,"readers_count":25,"score":25.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":4007,"topic_slug":"alternatives-to-dynamic-shadows","display_username":"Jonathan","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"GoldenThumbs","name":"Golden Thumbs","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/goldenthumbs/{size}/1669_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":669,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":34822,"name":"","username":"Dave82","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/dave82/{size}/2369_2.png","created_at":"2020-01-03T00:38:55.460Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThere are really no pre rendered engines out there at least no free, open source ones so this might be interesting toy for other old school enthusiast out there. And could bring in more Urho users/developers sooner or later.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Sinoid\" data-post=\"14\" data-topic=\"4007\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/f19dbf/40.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e Sinoid:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ehow fat is a single view (color + depth, etc)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWell if by fat you mean how much passes/layers are used , well there are a lot but with a standard (prepass / deferred etc) shading models there are no other solutions. At least i didn‚Äôt found so far. Performance wise i didn‚Äôt experienced any slowdowns even on an old GT 430 it runs perfectly fine\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe rendering looks like this :\u003cbr\u003e\nafter the base pass i render the occluders (z pass only) if the occluders can cast shadow there is an extra shadow pass (without a light pass) for each occluder so they can cast shadows on characters and other dynamic objects but not receive any light.\u003cbr\u003e\nThen there is a shadow caster light which only casts shadow on invisible occluders and use multiplicative blending  (this time dynamic objects use only a shadow pass but no light pass) Finally there is yet another light (same position and direction as the shadow caster but this affect only dynamic objects by illuminate them and cast shadow on each other)\u003cbr\u003e\nThe best thing is that i was affraid of how this will work with alpha passes ? Well , it works perfectly\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEven mixng the scene with additive lights is possible (imagine a flickering light like a fireplace or a short circuit illuminate and cast shadow in a pre rendered background scenario‚Ä¶ it would be a really cool effect).\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":15,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-01-03T00:41:04.753Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":14,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":28,"readers_count":27,"score":10.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":4007,"topic_slug":"alternatives-to-dynamic-shadows","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"ca